cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep convolutional networks and their application to computer vision tasks, specifically in the context of domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses techniques for stabilizing training in deep networks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep networks and domain adaptation also suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Squeeze-and-Excite modules, which are a type of neural network architecture, suggesting a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to histopathology and chest X-ray databases, suggesting a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
